The paper discusses the use of Artificial Immune Systems (AIS) for intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the Dendritic Cell Algorithm (DCA), which is a type of machine learning algorithm, and therefore could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the potential for the DCA to be used in real-time systems, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
